cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LOgic, cs.CL, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with internal dependently-typed higher-order logic and models of programming languages and program logics.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper constructs a model of a programming language with higher-order store and recursive types.
- cs.LOgic (Logic in Computer Science) is another possible category as the paper deals with modal operators and recursive definitions of terms, predicates, and types.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with natural language processing or computational linguistics.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a less likely category as the paper does not deal with information theory or coding theory.
